<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Biodiversity/Related-developments/Food-security-and-climate-change-the-answer-is-biodiversity" title="Food security and climate change: the answer is biodiversity " alt="link">Food security and climate change: the answer is biodiversity </a></h2>

	
					<p><b>Biodiversity is the key to global food security in a changing climate</b>By J. Cotter; R. Tirado; Greenpeace, Reliefweb, 2008. Climate change will profoundly affect agriculture and food security worldwide and will particularly impact smallholder farmers in poor countries. Based on a short review of recent scientific literature, this document argues that the most effective strategy to adapt agriculture to climate change is to increase biodiversity. </p>
