					<p>An East African regional network for the development of Biotechnology has announced plans aimed at promoting the application of biotechnology in agriculture, industry, and environmental management in Ethiopia. Shumu Teferra, BIO-EARN project and research coordinator says the project is working to develop a network of excellence that will significantly contribute to improve food security, sustainable environment management, industrial production and enhanced livelihood in Ethiopia. (Source: ASNS in Ethiopia, 10 January 2009) </p>
