						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Biodiversity/Related-developments/Wheat-yields-could-halve-by-2040" title="Wheat yields could halve by 2040" alt="link">Wheat yields could halve by 2040</a></h2>

	
					<p>Yields of non-organic wheat could fall from an average of 9 tonnes a hectare to 4 tonnes hectare sometime between 2040 and the end of this century as the planet runs out of phosphorus, a key part of the fertiliser needed to grow non-organic crops. Scarcity of phosphates are driving up the price, and sooner or later, as we inevitably start to run out of phosphates, non-organic yields will start a dramatic decline (Source: Sarah Dryden, New Consumer, 19 November 2008). </p>
