					<p>Nobel laureate Wangari Maathai on Wednesday urged upcoming talks on climate change to focus on protecting forests, especially rich treelands in the Congo Basin, Amazonia and Southeast Asia. &quot;African countries have to prioritise these issues. African environment ministers are working closely to come up with one African position.” (Source: AFP, 13 November 2008) </p>
