<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Biodiversity/Related-developments/Poor-policies-hamper-seed-trade-in-Eastern-Africa" title="Poor policies hamper seed trade in Eastern Africa" alt="link">Poor policies hamper seed trade in Eastern Africa</a></h2>

	
					<p>
Unfavourable seed policies, lengthy variety release process and controlled seed market have been identified as major constraints to seed sector in sub-Saharan Africa.
Limited access to suitable germplasm, technical constraints and limited access to production credit have been cited as major constraints to seed production in sub-Sahara Africa (Source: 
Henry Neondo, Africa Science News Service, 21 October 2008). </p>
